Plan Your Trip to Orange County: Best of Orange County Tourism

By Visit Laguna Beach

Orange County, California

Beyond its epic theme parks and perfect weather, Orange County is celebrated for outdoor dining, entertainment and beach-bound adventure. Treat yourself at South Coast Plaza for the finest in luxury shopping and superlative restaurants. Spend an afternoon aboard a whale watching cruise in Newport Harbor, or cast a reel from the Huntington Beach Pier. Stop to smell the flowers at the Sherman Library and Gardens, or explore Laguna’s vast variety of boutique shops along the Pacific Coast Highway.

Orange County travel advice

Powered by AI
These questions and answers were created by AI, using the most common questions travelers ask in the forums.

Family-Friendly Beaches

According to forum posts, Huntington Beach is highly recommended for families, especially with teenagers. It offers a youthful vibe, extensive bike trails, and activities like kite flying, volleyball, and surfing. The beach is also well-equipped with amenities like beach wheelchairs and has accessible parking lots close to the sand.

Alternative Beach Options

Some travelers suggested Newport Beach and Laguna Beach as great alternatives. Newport Beach offers a mix of upscale ambiance with quieter beaches, while Laguna Beach is praised for its scenic cliffs and artsy, walkable downtown area. Both locations provide a variety of dining options and are suitable for families looking for a more relaxed beach experience.

Special Considerations

For families concerned about accessibility, posts highlighted that beaches like Huntington and Newport provide adjacent parking and facilities to accommodate mobility issues, ensuring a comfortable experience for all family members.

Public Transit

According to forum posts, travelers can use Metrolink or Amtrak from Anaheim to Los Angeles, with both services sharing tracks and stopping at Union Station. Metrolink is noted for being part of the regional commuter rail system, whereas Metro is a separate entity under the Los Angeles Metropolitan Transportation Authority, useful for local transit within LA.

Rideshare and Taxis

Several users have discussed using rideshares like Uber or Lyft for direct transportation to destinations such as Warner Bros Studios or Disneyland from Anaheim. This option provides convenience but can be more expensive compared to public transit, especially for longer distances.

Shuttle Services

Some travelers mentioned the availability of shuttle services for specific destinations. For instance, there’s a free Burbank Bus that connects from the Metrolink station to Warner Bros Studios, highlighting a practical solution for travelers looking to reach specific tourist spots without a car.

Local Recommendations

For local Anaheim attractions, forum contributors have suggested using rideshares for short trips or even walking if staying near major attractions like Disneyland, providing flexibility and ease of movement around busy areas.
